F3X Uni-Timer V1.1.0

Updates:
1.  Removed bluetooth button functionality. The bluetooth button were not reliable and were prone to causing the system to crash.
2.  Added event management - creation and running of manual and F3XVault events, data logging for download, F3XVault upload.
3.  Revised and extended web pages
4.  Red button now exits back from menus
5.  Added Audio Unit capability.  The unit can operate as a remote audio unit for connection to a PA speaker
6.  Various small bug fixes
7.  Cleaned up some inconsistencies in the web pages
8.  fixed an issue in Practice Laps where turn beep may be missed due to lap time annoucement taking too long
9.  added a header line to the data file for flight downloads
10. updated functionality of the D1 and D2 expansion port inputs when external switches are connected
        
Known issues:
1.	Battery voltage display may not be accurate due to component tolerances.  It could be shown over or under value by 0.1 to 0.2V.
2.	When using the web pages the system may ocassionally crash and restart.

Planned features for future versions:
1.	Review historical flight data
2.	Anemometer integration

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Older Updates:

V1.0.7b
1.  Added automated base signalling for use with CD unit Diagnostic Flight function.  This is automated from th2 CD unit and requires no user intervention.

V1.0.6
1.  Improve readability of startup screen - larger fonts for unit type and IP address
2.  Removed wifi configuration manager to reduce confusion with wifi setup
3.  Updated Practice Laps mode - fixed code missing to accept base and camera signals
4.  Added actual volume value to options menu

V1.0.5
1.  improved stability of bluetooth button - now selectable between iTag and TrackerPA buttons (both green) - but may still occassionaly cause problems
2.  reduced audio latency (reduced button debounce time and removed blank audio at start of mp3 files)

V1.0.4
This version was not released.  Internal testing only.

V1.0.3
1.  added abiity to store multiple wifi router/hotspot credentials for easy switching.  Refer to wiki page: "F3X Uni Timer configuring for multiple wifi access points".
2.  added option to connect via wifi config manager if unable to connect using stored credentials (green=ignore, red=config manager)
3.  added option for auto restart time after prac flight - 10,15,20,30 secs
4.  improved stability of AP mode

V1.0.2
1.	Changed lap call to number only
2.  Added option for auto restart at end of proctice flight
3.  Enabled external button for CD mode
4.  Displays signal strength value on flight screen when configured as base unit

V1.0.1
1.	Wifi and bluetooth startup overide.
	Pressing the Green button when switching power on will overide wifi and bluetooth settings. Neither service will be started. 
2.	Wifi mode menu.
	New sub menu allowing selection of wifi mode then select save and restart.
3.	Bluetooth mode menu.
	New sub menu allowing selection of bluetooth mode (On or Off) and bluetooth button type (Single or Double), then select save and restart.
4.	Unit type menu.
	New submenu allowing selection of unit type (CD, Base A, Base B, Audio or Wind), then select Save and restart.
5.	Bases/camera signal strength display.
	The network signal strength (1-9) measured at the bases/cameras is display on the Bases setup menu 
	and the Flight screen (when flight not running). An X is shown if no connection.
6.	Updated system settings web page.
	Base and camera connections can be switched on/off.  Volume can be adjusted and battery voltage is shown.
7.	Updated practice flight web page.
	Expanded data displayed and fields are updated dynamically as flight progresses. Volume can be adjusted and battery voltage is shown.
